<body>

<div1 type="letter">
<pb facs="wfc.css00551"/>

<note type="letterhead">Buffalo Bill's Wild West<lb/>Pahaska Tepee.<lb/>Touring Great Britain.</note>


<opener><dateline>Oswestry<ref target="n01">1</ref><lb/>


May. 11<hi rend="sup">th</hi>1904</dateline>


<salute>My Dear <persName xml:id="beck.g">Beck</persName></salute></opener>


<p>I hope this may find you and yours well and happy. I am in excellent health&#8212; And business splendid. I wrote you from N. Y. So did Mr Clark<ref target="n02">2</ref> What the Hearst Estate<ref target="n03">3</ref> would do&#8212;</p>

<p>Please let me hear from you on the subject. </p>

<p>Hope there <choice><sic>wont</sic><corr>won't</corr></choice> be so much trouble about our <orgName xml:id="canal.cs">ditch</orgName> this summer.</p>


<closer><salute>Yours truly</salute>


<signed>W. F. Cody</signed></closer>
</div1>
</body>


<back>

<note xml:id="n01">Note 1: Buffalo Bill's Wild West performed in Oswestry, England, on May 11, 1904.</note>

<note xml:id="n02">Note 2: "Mr Clark" is Edward Hardy Clark (1864-1945), the financial manager for Phoebe Hearst. </note>

<note xml:id="n03">Note 3: The Hearst Estate provided an indemnity bond of $30,000 at 7.5% interest for the <orgName xml:id="company.si">Shoshone Irrigation Company</orgName> project.</note>
</back>
